      • listItemsAtAPath

        public FileStagingItemBulkResponse listItemsAtAPath(String item)
        List Items At A Path

        Return a list of files and folders for the specified path. Paths are different for Admin users (Vault Owners and System Admins) and non-Admin users.

        Parameters:
        item, - the file path of the item
        Returns:
        FileStagingItemBulkResponse
        Vault API Endpoint:
         GET /api/{version}/services/file_staging/items/{item}
        Vault API Help Link:
        https://developer.veevavault.com/api/23.2/#list-items-at-a-path
        Example Request:
        FileStagingItemBulkResponse resp = vaultClient.newRequest(FileStagingRequest.class).listItemsAtAPath("Documents");
        Example Response:
             for(FileStagingItem fileStagingItem : resp.getData()) {
         System.out.println(fileStagingItem);
     }

        public VaultResponse downloadItemContent(String item)
        Download Item Content

        Retrieve the content of a specified file from the file staging server. Use the Range header to create resumable downloads for large files, or to continue downloading a file if your session is interrupted.

        Parameters:
        item, - the file path of the item
        Returns:
        VaultResponse
        Vault API Endpoint:
         GET /api/{version}/services/file_staging/items/content/{item}
        Vault API Help Link:
        https://developer.veevavault.com/api/23.2/#get-item-content
        Example Request:
        VaultResponse resp = vaultClient.newRequest(FileStagingRequest.class).downloadItemContent("Documents/New/file.txt");
        Example Response:
         System.out.println(resp.getResponse());

      • createResumableUploadSession

        public FileStagingSessionResponse createResumableUploadSession(String path,
                                                               int size)
        Create Resumable Upload Session

        Initiate a multipart upload session and return an upload session ID. The upload_session_id, can use to upload file parts, resume an interrupted session, retrieve information about a session, and, if necessary, abort a session.

        Parameters:
        path, - the path to the item in the file staging area
        size, - the total size in bytes of the file
        Returns:
        FileStagingSessionResponse
        Vault API Endpoint:
         POST /api/{version}/services/file_staging/upload
        Vault API Help Link:
        https://developer.veevavault.com/api/23.2/#create-resumable-upload-session
        Example Request:
        FileStagingRequest fileStagingRequest = vaultClient.newRequest(FileStagingRequest.class);
        Example Response:
             FileStagingSessionResponse resp = fileStagingRequest.createResumableUploadSession(fileStagingResumableUploadSession);
     String uploadSessionId = resp.getData().getUploadSessionID();

      • uploadToASession

        public FileStagingSessionResponse uploadToASession(String uploadSessionId,
                                                   int partNumber)
        Upload to a Session

        The session owner can upload parts of a file to an active upload session. By default, you can upload up to 2000 parts per upload session, and each part can be up to 50MB. Use the Range header to specify the range of bytes for each upload, or split files into parts and add each part as a separate file. Each part must be the same size, except for the last part in the upload session.

        Parameters:
        uploadSessionId, - the session id of the resumable upload session
        partNumber - The part number, which uniquely identifies a file part and defines its position within the file as a whole.
        Returns:
        FileStagingSessionResponse
        Vault API Endpoint:
         PUT /api/{version}/services/file_staging/upload/{upload_session_id}
        Vault API Help Link:
        https://developer.veevavault.com/api/23.2/#upload-to-a-session
        Example Request:
             FileStagingRequest fileStagingRequest = vaultClient.newRequest(FileStagingRequest.class);
        Example Response:
             FileStagingSessionResponse resp = fileStagingRequest.uploadToASession(uploadSessionId, 1);

      • getUploadSessionDetails

        public FileStagingSessionResponse getUploadSessionDetails(String uploadSessionId)
        Get Session Details

        Retrieve the details of an active upload session. Admin users can get details for all sessions, while non-Admin users can only get details for sessions if they are the owner.

        Parameters:
        uploadSessionId, - the session id of the resumable upload session
        Returns:
        FileStagingSessionResponse
        Vault API Endpoint:
         GET /api/{version}/services/file_staging/upload/{upload_session_id}
        Vault API Help Link:
        https://developer.veevavault.com/api/23.2/#get-upload-session-details
        Example Request:
             FileStagingRequest fileStagingRequest = vaultClient.newRequest(FileStagingRequest.class);
        Example Response:
            FileStagingSessionResponse resp = fileStagingRequest.getUploadSessionDetails(uploadSessionId);
    System.out.println(resp.getSession().getCreatedDate());

      • abortUploadSession

        public VaultResponse abortUploadSession(String uploadSessionId)
        Abort Upload Session

        Abort an active upload session and purge all uploaded file parts. Admin users can see and abort all upload sessions, while non-Admin users can only see and abort sessions where they are the owner.

        Parameters:
        uploadSessionId, - the session id of the resumable upload session
        Returns:
        VaultResponse
        Vault API Endpoint:
         DELETE /api/{version}/services/file_staging/upload/{upload_session_id}
        Vault API Help Link:
        https://developer.veevavault.com/api/23.2/#abort-upload-session
        Example Request:
             FileStagingRequest fileStagingRequest = vaultClient.newRequest(FileStagingRequest.class);
        Example Response:
             VaultResponse resp =  fileStagingRequest.abortUploadSession(uploadSessionId);
